properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A wet start to the week. Locations: South coast of Newfoundland. Time span: Tonight through Tuesday. Remarks: A moist, tropical airmass capable of producing heavy downpours will persist over the south coast of Newfoundland into Tuesday. Periods of heavy rain can then be expected until Tuesday afternoon when a cold front is expected to move through the region, thereby cutting off the moisture supply. A rainfall warning is in effect for the Burgeo - Ramea area. Please continue to monitor subsequent forecasts as additional rainfall warnings may be required. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Warm and humid conditions expected this afternoon and evening. A warm and humid air mass is expected to move into portions of northwestern Ontario near the Minnesota border this afternoon. Afternoon highs in the upper twenties will combine with the humidity to create humidex values in the mid thirties. Temperatures on Tuesday should be a few degrees cooler with lesser humidity. These conditions pose a health risk when you are not used to the heat. Everyone is at risk from heat, especially older adults, infants and young children, and people with chronic illnesses. You are advised to 1) drink plenty of cool liquids before feeling thirsty; and 2) keep cool by dressing for the weather and spending a few hours each day in a cool place. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
